year = 2000

# To get year (integer input) from the user
# year = int(input("Enter a year: "))

if (year % 4) == 0:
   if (year % 100) == 0:
       if (year % 400) == 0:
           print("{0} is a leap year".format(year))
       else:
           print("{0} is not a leap year".format(year))
   else:
       print("{0} is a leap year".format(year))
else:
   print("{0} is not a leap year".format(year)) You can change the value of in the source code and run it again to test this program. Check if a Number is Odd or Even Find Armstrong Number in an Interval Find Numbers Divisible by Another Number Join our newsletter for the latest updates. Join our newsletter for the latest updates. Java
